hwIFExtMib.name: hwIFExtMib

revisions.description: V2.52 Update hwTrunkIfModel, add object-type l4(20).
V2.51 add hwTrunkMemberCountUpperThreshold hwTrunkMemberCountLowerThreshold hwExtTrunkMemberCountExceedThreshold hwExtTrunkMemberCountExceedThresholdResume range.
Update hwLogicIfType , add object-type globalVe(26), subGlobalVe(27).
Update hwTrunkIfWorkingMode, modify object-type lacpStaticMode(3) to lacpMode(3) and add object-type lacpCompatibleMode(4).
Update hwTrunkIfWorkingMode, modify object-type lacpMode(3) to lacpStaticMode(3); Update hwLogicIfType, add object-type subPosFr(25).
Update the hwLinkDownReason, add from veFlowDown to negotiationUnsupported.
Update the hwLogicIfType, add globalImaGroup and subGlobalImaGroup.
Update the hwLogicIfType, add remoteAp, vBridge,atmBundle and mtunnel.

hwIFExtMib.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwIFExtMib.description: Some attribute of interface extended content, information of interface IP, interface of trunk interface.

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

HWDirectionType.name: HWDirectionType
HWDirectionType.description: The Direction Flux Limit apply on.

hwIFExtTable.name: hwIFExtTable
hwIFExtTable.description: Interface extended table of private mib.

hwIFExtEntry.name: hwIFExtEntry
hwIFExtEntry.description: Entries of private extended interface table.

hwIFExtIndex.name: hwIFExtIndex
hwIFExtIndex.description: Index of extended table of interface.

hwIFExtLayer.name: hwIFExtLayer
hwIFExtLayer.description: Switch the port between Layer3 and Layer2. Corresponding to the port switch command.Layer2(1) is 1 when the port switch from layer3 to layer2.Layer3(1) is 1 when the port switch from lyaer2 to layer3.

hwIFExtFrameType.name: hwIFExtFrameType
hwIFExtFrameType.description: Frame type is accepted by VLAN virtual interfaces.Frame format contains ethernetII(1),ethernetII(2),ethernet8022(3),ethernet8023. The type location setting 1 when the ethernetII(1) type is accepted.Now only surpport the first(ethernetII(1))

hwIFExtFlowStatInterval.name: hwIFExtFlowStatInterval
hwIFExtFlowStatInterval.description: Interval of interface flow stat.The value of interval must be divided exactly by 10.The interface interval is effective,when both interface interval and global interval are config.Globle interval is only effective in interfaces,which interface interval is not configured. The real time property of interface flow stat rate will be affected by the value of interval.

hwIFExtFlushReceiveEnable.name: hwIFExtFlushReceiveEnable
hwIFExtFlushReceiveEnable.description: Whether or not permit the port to take over FLUSHDUs. Once it is enabled, the port will take over SmartLink FlushDUs from related vlans so as to delete the MAC forwarding table in the local equipment.

hwIFExtFlushVlanId.name: hwIFExtFlushVlanId
hwIFExtFlushVlanId.description: The ID of Vlan the port belongs to.When it is 0, it indicates the function of receiving FlushPDU is disabled.

hwIFExtFlushPasswd.name: hwIFExtFlushPasswd
hwIFExtFlushPasswd.description: A 16-octet read-write value used to define the password for negotiation.

hwIFExtFlowStatus.name: hwIFExtFlowStatus
hwIFExtFlowStatus.description: Current flow status of interface. 1:flow up 2:flow down

hwIFExtMtu.name: hwIFExtMtu
hwIFExtMtu.description: The Max Transmit Unit of the interface.

hwIFExtMacAddr.name: hwIFExtMacAddr
hwIFExtMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the interface .

hwIFExtBlockPriority.name: hwIFExtBlockPriority
hwIFExtBlockPriority.description: The blocked priority of the interface.

hwIFExtMacShift.name: hwIFExtMacShift
hwIFExtMacShift.description: The mac-shift state of the interface. 1:normal 2:monitor mac-shift

hwIFExtSuppressStatus.name: hwIFExtSuppressStatus
hwIFExtSuppressStatus.description: The suppress state of the interface. 0:unsuppress 1:suppress

hwIFExtPoisonReverse.name: hwIFExtPoisonReverse
hwIFExtPoisonReverse.description: Whether or not enable Split-horizon forwarding

hwIFExtInputPktRate.name: hwIFExtInputPktRate
hwIFExtInputPktRate.description: This object indicates the rate of the incoming packets on an interface. The rate value is 64 bits. hwIFExtInputPktRate indicates the lower 32 bits, while hwIFExtInputHighPktRate indicates the higher 32 bits.

hwIFExtInputHighPktRate.name: hwIFExtInputHighPktRate
hwIFExtInputHighPktRate.description: This object indicates the rate of the incoming packets on an interface. The rate value is 64 bits. hwIFExtInputPktRate indicates the lower 32 bits, while hwIFExtInputHighPktRate indicates the higher 32 bits.

hwIFExtOutputPktRate.name: hwIFExtOutputPktRate
hwIFExtOutputPktRate.description: This object indicates the rate of the outgoing packets on an interface. The rate value is 64 bits. hwIFExtOutputPktRate indicates the lower 32 bits, while hwIFExtOutputHighPktRate indicates the higher 32 bits.

hwIFExtOutputHighPktRate.name: hwIFExtOutputHighPktRate
hwIFExtOutputHighPktRate.description: This object indicates the rate of the outgoing packets on an interface. The rate value is 64 bits. hwIFExtOutputPktRate indicates the lower 32 bits, while hwIFExtOutputHighPktRate indicates the higher 32 bits.

hwIFExtInputOctetRate.name: hwIFExtInputOctetRate
hwIFExtInputOctetRate.description: This object indicates the octet rate of the incoming traffic on an interface. The rate value is 64 bits. hwIFExtInputOctetRate indicates the lower 32 bits, while hwIFExtInputHighOctetRate indicates the higher 32 bits.

hwIFExtInputHighOctetRate.name: hwIFExtInputHighOctetRate
hwIFExtInputHighOctetRate.description: This object indicates the octet rate of the incoming traffic on an interface. The rate value is 64 bits. hwIFExtInputOctetRate indicates the lower 32 bits, while hwIFExtInputHighOctetRate indicates the higher 32 bits.

hwIFExtOutputOctetRate.name: hwIFExtOutputOctetRate
hwIFExtOutputOctetRate.description: This object indicates the octet rate of the outgoing traffic on an interface. The rate value is 64 bits. hwIFExtOutputOctetRate indicates the lower 32 bits, while hwIFExtOutputHighOctetRate indicates the higher 32 bits.

hwIFExtOutputHighOctetRate.name: hwIFExtOutputHighOctetRate
hwIFExtOutputHighOctetRate.description: This object indicates the octet rate of the outgoing traffic on an interface. The rate value is 64 bits. hwIFExtOutputOctetRate indicates the lower 32 bits, while hwIFExtOutputHighOctetRate indicates the higher 32 bits.

hwIFExtSwitchPortIndex.name: hwIFExtSwitchPortIndex
hwIFExtSwitchPortIndex.description: Number of layer2 interface port, a unique value, for each port.It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

hwIFExtSuppressStatusIPv6.name: hwIFExtSuppressStatusIPv6
hwIFExtSuppressStatusIPv6.description: The suppress state of the interface(IPv6). 0:unsuppress 1:suppress

hwIFExtPhyStatus.name: hwIFExtPhyStatus
hwIFExtPhyStatus.description: The physical status of member interface.

hwIFExtMemberOf.name: hwIFExtMemberOf
hwIFExtMemberOf.description: The description of the main interface which has the membership with the member interface.

hwLinkModeChangeAutoCreateIfTable.name: hwLinkModeChangeAutoCreateIfTable
hwLinkModeChangeAutoCreateIfTable.description: Interface extended table of private mib.

hwLinkModeChangeAutoCreateIfEntry.name: hwLinkModeChangeAutoCreateIfEntry
hwLinkModeChangeAutoCreateIfEntry.description: Entries of private extended interface table.

hwAutoIfIndex.name: hwAutoIfIndex
hwAutoIfIndex.description: Index of extended table of interface.

hwNewIfTimeslot.name: hwNewIfTimeslot
hwNewIfTimeslot.description: The time slot of the TDM interface: timeslot0(0):The time slot 0 on the TDM interface, timeslot1(1):The time slot 1 on the TDM interface, timeslot2(2):The time slot 2 on the TDM interface, timeslot3(3):The time slot 3 on the TDM interface, timeslot4(4):The time slot 4 on the TDM interface, timeslot5(5):The time slot 5 on the TDM interface, timeslot6(6):The time slot 6 on the TDM interface, timeslot7(7):The time slot 7 on the TDM interface, timeslot8(8):The time slot 8 on the TDM interface, timeslot9(9):The time slot 9 on the TDM interface, timeslot10(10):The time slot 10 on the TDM interface, timeslot11(11):The time slot 11 on the TDM interface, timeslot12(12):The time slot 12 on the TDM interface, timeslot13(13):The time slot 13 on the TDM interface, timeslot14(14):The time slot 14 on the TDM interface, timeslot15(15):The time slot 15 on the TDM interface, timeslot16(16):The time slot 16 on the TDM interface, timeslot17(17):The time slot 17 on the TDM interface, timeslot18(18):The time slot 18 on the TDM interface, timeslot19(19):The time slot 19 on the TDM interface, timeslot20(20):The time slot 20 on the TDM interface, timeslot21(21):The time slot 21 on the TDM interface, timeslot22(22):The time slot 22 on the TDM interface, timeslot23(23):The time slot 23 on the TDM interface, timeslot24(24):The time slot 24 on the TDM interface, timeslot25(25):The time slot 25 on the TDM interface, timeslot26(26):The time slot 26 on the TDM interface, timeslot27(27):The time slot 27 on the TDM interface, timeslot28(28):The time slot 28 on the TDM interface, timeslot29(29):The time slot 29 on the TDM interface, timeslot30(30):The time slot 30 on the TDM interface, timeslot31(31):The time slot 31 on the TDM interface.

hwIFExtPhyNumber.name: hwIFExtPhyNumber
hwIFExtPhyNumber.description: The number of the physical interfaces.

hwIfIpTable.name: hwIfIpTable
hwIfIpTable.description: Interface IP address configuration table .It contains IP address, IP address mask, IP address acquiring method.

hwIpAdEntAddr.name: hwIpAdEntAddr
hwIpAdEntAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

hwIpAdEntIfIndex.name: hwIpAdEntIfIndex
hwIpAdEntIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

hwIpAdEntNetMask.name: hwIpAdEntNetMask
hwIpAdEntNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the host bits set to 0.

hwIpAdEntBcastAddr.name: hwIpAdEntBcastAddr
hwIpAdEntBcastAddr.description: The value of the least-significant bit in the IP broadcast address used for sending datagrams on the (logical) interface associated with the IP address of this entry. For example, when the Internet standard all-ones broadcast address is used, the value will be 1. This value applies to both the subnet and network broadcasts addresses used by the entity on this (logical) interface.

hwIpAdEntReasmMaxSize.name: hwIpAdEntReasmMaxSize
hwIpAdEntReasmMaxSize.description: The size of the largest IP datagram which this entity can re-assemble from incoming IP fragmented datagram received on this interface.

hwIpAdEntAddressType.name: hwIpAdEntAddressType
hwIpAdEntAddressType.description: The flag indicates whether the IP address is primary IP address. One interface has only one primary IP address, but can have many sub IP address. So when add a primary IP address to an interface that has already a primary IP address, the new primary address will replace old primary address and the old primary address will be deleted.

hwIfIpMethod.name: hwIfIpMethod
hwIfIpMethod.description: Interface IP address acquiring method. assignedIp(1) indicates that the address was manually configured to a specified address, for example, by user configuration. dhcpIp(2) indicates an address that was assigned to this system by a DHCP server. bootpIp(3) indicates an address that was assigned to this system by the bootp protocol. other(4) indicates an address created by another method. linklayer(5) indicates an address created by IPv6 stateless auto-configuration. random(6) indicates an address chosen by the system at random, for example, an IPv4 address within 169.254/16, or an RFC 3041 privacy address.

hwIfIpUnnumberedTable.name: hwIfIpUnnumberedTable
hwIfIpUnnumberedTable.description: Interface IP address unnumbered table. It contains lend IP address and lend IP address mask.

hwUnnumberedIfIndex.name: hwUnnumberedIfIndex
hwUnnumberedIfIndex.description: The index value of the unnumbered interface.

hwLendIfIndex.name: hwLendIfIndex
hwLendIfIndex.description: The index value of the lend interface.

hwLendIpAddr.name: hwLendIpAddr
hwLendIpAddr.description: The IP address of the lend interface.

hwLendIpAddrNetMask.name: hwLendIpAddrNetMask
hwLendIpAddrNetMask.description: The IP address mask of the lend interface.

hwIfIpAddrTable.name: hwIfIpAddrTable
hwIfIpAddrTable.description: This table contains addressing information relevant to the entity's interfaces.

hwIfIpAddrEntIfIndex.name: hwIfIpAddrEntIfIndex
hwIfIpAddrEntIfIndex.description: The index value that uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IF-MIB's ifIndex.

hwIfIpAddrEntAddr.name: hwIfIpAddrEntAddr
hwIfIpAddrEntAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

hwIfIpAddrEntPrefix.name: hwIfIpAddrEntPrefix
hwIfIpAddrEntPrefix.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the host bits set to 0.

hwIfIpAddrEntOrigin.name: hwIfIpAddrEntOrigin
hwIfIpAddrEntOrigin.description: Interface IP address acquiring method. assignedIp(1) indicates that the address was manually configured to a specified address, for example, by user configuration. dhcpIp(2) indicates an address that was assigned to this system by a DHCP server. bootpIp(3) indicates an address that was assigned to this system by the bootp protocol. other(4) indicates an address created by another method. linklayer(5) indicates an address created by IPv6 stateless auto-configuration. random(6) indicates an address chosen by the system at random, for example, an IPv4 address within 169.254/16, or an RFC 3041 privacy address.

hwIfIpAddrEntStatus.name: hwIfIpAddrEntStatus
hwIfIpAddrEntStatus.description: The status of the address, describing if the address can be used for communication. In the absence of other information, an IPv4 address is always preferred(1).

hwIfIpAddrEntCreated.name: hwIfIpAddrEntCreated
hwIfIpAddrEntCreated.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this entry was created. If this entry was created prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

hwIfIpAddrEntLastChanged.name: hwIfIpAddrEntLastChanged
hwIfIpAddrEntLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this entry was last updated. If this entry was updated prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

hwIfIpAddrEntBcastAddr.name: hwIfIpAddrEntBcastAddr
hwIfIpAddrEntBcastAddr.description: The value of the least-significant bit in the IP broadcast address used for sending datagrams on the (logical) interface associated with the IP address of this entry. For example, when the Internet standard all-ones broadcast address is used, the value will be 1. This value applies to both the subnet and network broadcasts addresses used by the entity on this (logical) interface.

hwIfIpAddrEntReasmMaxSize.name: hwIfIpAddrEntReasmMaxSize
hwIfIpAddrEntReasmMaxSize.description: The size of the largest IP datagram which this entity can re-assemble from incoming IP fragmented datagram received on this interface.

hwIfIpAddrEntAddrType.name: hwIfIpAddrEntAddrType
hwIfIpAddrEntAddrType.description: The flag indicates whether the IP address is primary IP address.

hwIfIpAddrEntVpn.name: hwIfIpAddrEntVpn
hwIfIpAddrEntVpn.description: The vpn name of ip address.The public address does not have any value.

hwTrunkNextIndex.name: hwTrunkNextIndex
hwTrunkNextIndex.description: The nextindex of Trunk interface,that means its position

hwTrunkIndex.name: hwTrunkIndex
hwTrunkIndex.description: The number of the Trunk interface

hwTrunkIfID.name: hwTrunkIfID
hwTrunkIfID.description: The identification of the Trunk interface.It may identify Trunk and is an index of the interface.

hwTrunkIfType.name: hwTrunkIfType
hwTrunkIfType.description: The type of the Trunk interface includes eth-trunk and ip-trunk. The ip-trunk is only comprised by pos link, otherwise the eth-trunk is only comprised by ethernet link.

hwTrunkIfIndex.name: hwTrunkIfIndex
hwTrunkIfIndex.description: Index number of the Trunk interface,it is consistent with ifIndex of ifTable in IF-MIB.

hwTrunkIfModel.name: hwTrunkIfModel
hwTrunkIfModel.description: Participated model of interface load. sourceDesMac(2) and sourceMac(10) and desMac(11) are Layer2 hash arithmetic.

hwTrunkIfBandWidthAffectLinkNum.name: hwTrunkIfBandWidthAffectLinkNum
hwTrunkIfBandWidthAffectLinkNum.description: The max bandwidth-affected-linknumber, by default, an Eth-Trunk interface has a maximum of 16 physical interfaces. The number of physical interfaces in an Eth-Trunk interface varies according to the product type.Only in layer 2,can set this value.

hwTrunkIfMinLinkNum.name: hwTrunkIfMinLinkNum
hwTrunkIfMinLinkNum.description: The Trunk port changes to up when the number of the up port reach hwTrunkIfMinLinkNum.

hwTrunkIfRowStatus.name: hwTrunkIfRowStatus
hwTrunkIfRowStatus.description: Current operation status of the row

hwTrunkIfWorkingMode.name: hwTrunkIfWorkingMode
hwTrunkIfWorkingMode.description: Current working mode of trunk. 1:master/backup access mode 2:normal mode 3:lacp static mode 4:lacp compatible mode 5:port standby mode

hwTrunkIfWorkingState.name: hwTrunkIfWorkingState
hwTrunkIfWorkingState.description: Current working state of backup-access trunk. 1:general mode working state 2:initialization 3:master working 4:backup working

hwTrunkIfAutoRecover.name: hwTrunkIfAutoRecover
hwTrunkIfAutoRecover.description: If auto-recover has been set, the master port will be working instead of the other port when it changes from down state to up state. 1: don't support auto-recover 2: support auto-recover

hwTrunkIfPreemptEnable.name: hwTrunkIfPreemptEnable
hwTrunkIfPreemptEnable.description: The preemption according to the priority will be and only be enabled when the lag port is working in static mode(M:N backup mode) In default condition, the preemption is disabled.

hwTrunkIfPreemptDelay.name: hwTrunkIfPreemptDelay
hwTrunkIfPreemptDelay.description: The waiting time for priority preemption; Unit: second. It is enabled only when the priority preemption is enabled. It indicates, When it comes to priority preemption, the operation of preemption will be delayed for hwTrunkIfPreemptDelay time. The specific minimum specification depends on products.

hwTrunkIfTimeoutReceive.name: hwTrunkIfTimeoutReceive
hwTrunkIfTimeoutReceive.description: The expired time for the port to receive LACPDUS. There are two types: 1.fast: The default value is customized with products. 2.slow: 90 seconds

hwTrunkIfFlushSendEnable.name: hwTrunkIfFlushSendEnable
hwTrunkIfFlushSendEnable.description: Whether or not permit the trunk to transmit FlushDUs.It is only used when it is in the handwork 1:1 mode.Once it is enabled, the newly active interface in the trunk will send SmartLink FlushDUs so as to delete the related MAC forwarding table of the layer2 equipment in network.Otherwise, SmartLink FlushDUs will not be sent.

hwTrunkIfFlushVlanId.name: hwTrunkIfFlushVlanId
hwTrunkIfFlushVlanId.description: The ID of Vlan the partner port belongs to.When it is 0, it indicates the function of sending FlushPDU is disabled.

hwTrunkIfFlushPasswd.name: hwTrunkIfFlushPasswd
hwTrunkIfFlushPasswd.description: A 16-octet read-create value used to define the password for negotiation.

hwTrunkIfForceSwitchEnable.name: hwTrunkIfForceSwitchEnable
hwTrunkIfForceSwitchEnable.description: It is only used when it is in the handwork 1:1 mode and the current working link is the backup link. At that time, working link will move from backup link to master link. However, if the master link is down, the operation will be forbidden.

hwTrunkIfStatReset.name: hwTrunkIfStatReset
hwTrunkIfStatReset.description: Reset the statistic information of LACPDUsRx,MarkerPDUsRx,LACPDUsTx, MarkerResponsePDUsTx for all the ports in the current trunk.

hwTrunkBandwidth.name: hwTrunkBandwidth
hwTrunkBandwidth.description: Current bandwidth of trunk in units of 1,000,000 bits per second. This bandwidth is the peculiar property of Eth-Trunk. And to the other kinds of trunk, this bandwidth is -1.

hwTrunkIfArpSendSpeed.name: hwTrunkIfArpSendSpeed
hwTrunkIfArpSendSpeed.description: Indicates the rate of sending gratuitous ARP packets (in pkts/sec) on the trunk member interface.

hwTrunkIfLagSelectedPortStd.name: hwTrunkIfLagSelectedPortStd
hwTrunkIfLagSelectedPortStd.description: The static mode Eth-trunk selected port standard. There are two types: 1.speed : selected by port's speed 2.priority: selected by port's priority The default type is priority.

hwTrunkIfLagMaxActiveLinkNum.name: hwTrunkIfLagMaxActiveLinkNum
hwTrunkIfLagMaxActiveLinkNum.description: The static mode Eth-trunk selected ports can not more than the value.

hwTrunkETrunkSysID.name: hwTrunkETrunkSysID
hwTrunkETrunkSysID.description: The system ID of the E-Trunk. If set ffff-ffff-ffff the system ID will be to default.

hwTrunkETrunkPriorityReset.name: hwTrunkETrunkPriorityReset
hwTrunkETrunkPriorityReset.description: Status of operation, there are yes(1) and no(2). It expresses whether the configure of E-Trunk priority is resetted.

hwTrunkETrunkSysIDReset.name: hwTrunkETrunkSysIDReset
hwTrunkETrunkSysIDReset.description: Status of operation, there are yes(1) and no(2). It expresses whether the configure of E-Trunk system ID is resetted.

hwTrunkLocalPrefMode.name: hwTrunkLocalPrefMode
hwTrunkLocalPrefMode.description: Local-preference transmit mode of eth-trunk, there are enable(1) and disable(2).The default value is enable(1).

hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpVrid.name: hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpVrid
hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpVrid.description: The VRID which the static mode Eth-trunk tracked to.

hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpIfIndex.name: hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpIfIndex
hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpIfIndex.description: The VRRP interface which the static mode Eth-trunk tracked to.

hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpReset.name: hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpReset
hwTrunkIfTrackVrrpReset.description: Status of operation, there are yes(1) and no(2). The value of this object identifies whether the operation of clearing the configuration is performed. And the configuration is that the Eth-Trunk interface in static LACP mode is associated with an mVRRP backup group. The value yes(1) indicates performing the operation. This object indicates one operation but not one status, so when the operation is performed, the value is no(2). By default, the value is no(2).

hwTrunkIfBackupPreemptEnable.name: hwTrunkIfBackupPreemptEnable
hwTrunkIfBackupPreemptEnable.description: The preemption according to the master and slave port will be and only be enabled when eth-trunk is working in backup mode. In default condition, the preemption is disabled.

hwTrunkIfBackupPreemptDelay.name: hwTrunkIfBackupPreemptDelay
hwTrunkIfBackupPreemptDelay.description: The waiting time for priority preemption; Unit: minute. It is enabled only when the priority preemption is enabled. It indicates, When it comes to priority preemption, the operation of preemption will be delayed for hwTrunkIfBackupPreemptDelay time.

hwTrunkIfCrcErrorSwitchEnable.name: hwTrunkIfCrcErrorSwitchEnable
hwTrunkIfCrcErrorSwitchEnable.description: make trunk member port stop in use if the port have crc error exceed the config threshold, the trunk would be down if member port in use is low

hwTrunkIfLagTimeOut.name: hwTrunkIfLagTimeOut
hwTrunkIfLagTimeOut.description: The expired time(Unit is second) of the port to receive LACPDUS in the fast mode. The hwTrunkIfTimeoutReceive is the type of timeout and use hwTrunkIfLagTimeOut to change time in the fast mode. The default value is customized with products. If the mode is not fast, the value is always 0.

hwTrunkMemCount.name: hwTrunkMemCount
hwTrunkMemCount.description: The count of Trunk member interfaces per Trunk.

hwTrunkUnknownUnicastIfModel.name: hwTrunkUnknownUnicastIfModel
hwTrunkUnknownUnicastIfModel.description: Participated model of load for unknown unicast. sourceDesMac(2) and sourceMac(10) and desMac(11) are Layer2 hash arithmetic.

hwTrunkETrunkSystemPriority.name: hwTrunkETrunkSystemPriority
hwTrunkETrunkSystemPriority.description: The system priority of the E-Trunk.

hwTrunkETrunkSystemID.name: hwTrunkETrunkSystemID
hwTrunkETrunkSystemID.description: The system ID of the E-Trunk. If set ffff-ffff-ffff the system ID will be to default.

hwTrunkCount.name: hwTrunkCount
hwTrunkCount.description: Number of configured trunk interfaces on the device.

hwTrunkMemberCountUpperThreshold.name: hwTrunkMemberCountUpperThreshold
hwTrunkMemberCountUpperThreshold.description: Upper threshold for the number of members of the Eth-Trunk in LACP mode.

hwTrunkMemberCountLowerThreshold.name: hwTrunkMemberCountLowerThreshold
hwTrunkMemberCountLowerThreshold.description: Lower threshold for the number of members of the Eth-Trunk in LACP mode.

hwTrunkSelectStatus.name: hwTrunkSelectStatus
hwTrunkSelectStatus.description: Selected Status of Trunk Port.It is used LACP.

hwTrunkLacpStatus.name: hwTrunkLacpStatus
hwTrunkLacpStatus.description: It is status of the LACP.

hwTrunkDeleteFlag.name: hwTrunkDeleteFlag
hwTrunkDeleteFlag.description: Flag is set trunk_del_enable(1) or trunk_del_disable(2), according to operation.

hwTrunkOperstatus.name: hwTrunkOperstatus
hwTrunkOperstatus.description: Status of operation, indicates port status. There are trunk_up(1) and trunk_down(2).It expresses whether port is shutdown.

hwTrunkIsDefaultLagRecv.name: hwTrunkIsDefaultLagRecv
hwTrunkIsDefaultLagRecv.description: We don't sustain now, default value is false.

hwTrunkPortWeight.name: hwTrunkPortWeight
hwTrunkPortWeight.description: Port weight, it expresses proportion of port in Trunk interface table

hwTrunkPortStandby.name: hwTrunkPortStandby
hwTrunkPortStandby.description: The value is backup of Trunk Port.

hwTrunkRowStatus.name: hwTrunkRowStatus
hwTrunkRowStatus.description: Current operation status of the row.

hwTrunkPortMaster.name: hwTrunkPortMaster
hwTrunkPortMaster.description: Master port of backup-access eth-trunk or not 1: port-slave 2: port-master

hwTrunkPortPriority.name: hwTrunkPortPriority
hwTrunkPortPriority.description: The priority value assigned to this Trunk Port. This 16-bit value is read-write.

hwTrunkPortStatReset.name: hwTrunkPortStatReset
hwTrunkPortStatReset.description: Reset the statistic information of LACPDUsRx,MarkerPDUsRx,LACPDUsTx, MarkerResponsePDUsTx for the current port.

hwTrunkPortLacpMode.name: hwTrunkPortLacpMode
hwTrunkPortLacpMode.description: The mode of port joining Lacp.

hwIFFlowStatGlobalInterval.name: hwIFFlowStatGlobalInterval
hwIFFlowStatGlobalInterval.description: Global interval of interface flow stat.The interface interval is effective, when both interface interval and global interval are config.Globle interval is only effective in interfaces,which interface interval is not configged. Flow stat rate of interface will be affected by the value of interval. The default value is 300s.

hwIfEtherStatEntry.name: hwIfEtherStatEntry
hwIfEtherStatEntry.description: Entry of Ethernet Interface Statistic Table

hwIfEtherStatInPkts64Octets.name: hwIfEtherStatInPkts64Octets
hwIfEtherStatInPkts64Octets.description: The number of recieved Packets whose size over 1518 bytes

hwIfEtherStatInPkts65to127Octets.name: hwIfEtherStatInPkts65to127Octets
hwIfEtherStatInPkts65to127Octets.description: The number of recieved Packets whose size over 1518 bytes

hwIfEtherStatInPkts128to255Octets.name: hwIfEtherStatInPkts128to255Octets
hwIfEtherStatInPkts128to255Octets.description: The number of recieved Packets whose size over 1518 bytes

hwIfEtherStatInPkts256to511Octets.name: hwIfEtherStatInPkts256to511Octets
hwIfEtherStatInPkts256to511Octets.description: The number of recieved Packets whose size over 1518 bytes

hwIfEtherStatInPkts512to1023Octets.name: hwIfEtherStatInPkts512to1023Octets
hwIfEtherStatInPkts512to1023Octets.description: The number of recieved Packets whose size over 1518 bytes

Index: hwTrunkIndex.
